<em> </em><em><strong>THE GRADUATES OF THIS PROGRAM ALSO RECEIVE:</strong></em></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><em><strong>Clinical Esthetics Certificate of Excellence</strong></em></li>\r\n 	<li><em><strong>Advanced Makeup Certificate</strong></em></li>\r\n 	<li><em><strong>Laser Certificate of Attendance (provided by AMMP)</strong></em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<em><strong> </strong></em><em><strong>The certificates are a recognition</strong></em><strong><em> of the student’s accomplishments!</em></strong>\r\n<h3 class=\"cufon_headings\"><em><strong>ADVANCED </strong></em><strong><em>CLINICAL ESTHETICS PRESENTATIONS AND HANDS-ON TREATMENTS ARE A PART OF OUR CURRICULUM AT NO ADDITIONAL COST! </em></strong><strong><em>(SEE THE LIST OF THE PROCEDURES LEARNED BELOW)</em></strong></h3>\r\n<strong>Our in-depth presentations based on the medical sources and new researches in the medical field.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>We provide our students with extraordinary skills, extensive in-depth knowledge, and confidence needed for a personal success and successful employment!</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Although Estheticians cannot operate laser in Illinois, we believe that every person practicing Skin Care needs to have an extensive knowledge on the technologies used in skin care and a medical setting. </strong><strong>Laser class for our students is provided by our partners and professionals in Laser technology: AAMP.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Students who want to gain additional expertise for work in medical settings, have the opportunity to also enroll</strong><strong> in the <a href=\"http://design-austin.com/ita/ma-program-description/\"><em><u>Medical Assisting Program</u></em></a><u>!</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Our Nationally Certified MA students are able to complete their externship at</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Rush University Medical School’s Dermatology Department. </strong><strong><u>In Illinois, Medical Assistants can be delegated by a Physician to perform Laser and Injections!</u></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Our advanced 750-hour Esthetics Program trains Estheticians (Aestheticians) in the study of the skin, skin care and treatments created to treat skin and its conditions. </strong><strong>An Esthetician cannot diagnose or treat skin diseases!</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><strong>The Esthetics Program consists of 750 hours of training and is dedicated to training superior-level</strong> <strong>Estheticians, able to work in a medical or a regular spa settings. The Program enhances each student’s personal development through its small class sizes, advanced curriculum, and extensive hands-on practice.</strong>The program extends to include a variety of facial procedures, microdermabrasion, chemical peeling, anti-aging treatments, rejuvenating techniques, body wraps, salt glows for the body, feet and hands treatments, waxing as a form of hair removal from the various parts of the body, including Brazilian hands on, cosmetic product knowledge, make-up techniques, and other advanced services.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>By giving students skills and confidence needed to succeed, the program prepares professionals of the highest caliber for a thriving career in any setting.</strong><strong> </strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Program is taught in ITA’s facility</strong><strong>, which has been set up to create the most effective and efficient learning environment for visual, auditory, and tactile learners!</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong><strong>Our advanced 750-hour Esthetics program includes basic and various advanced procedures and techniques.</strong> <strong><em>Additional</em></strong> <strong><em>Advanced hands on treatments and presentations <u>are included in our program  </u></em></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>The graduates of this program receive Clinical Esthetics Certificate of Excellence!</em></strong>\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\"><strong>Upcoming Start Dates</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>Day/Full-time: </strong>Monday – Thursday, 9 a.m. – 3:30 p.m.;<strong> September 6, 2016</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Evening/Part-time: </strong>Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, 9 a.m. – 3:30 p.m<strong>.; September 6, 2016</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Program takes</strong><strong> approximately 6 months </strong><strong>for full-time students</strong><strong> and approximately 9 months </strong><strong>for part-time students.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Upon successful completion of the Esthetics Program, graduates are eligible to sign up for the State licensing exams. </strong><strong>We are proud that our graduates have a 100% passing rate in Illinois and have some of the highest test scores nationally.</strong>\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\"><strong>Certification and Licensure</strong></h2>\r\n<strong>Students, who complete the entire 750-hour Program, receive the following:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Esthetics Diploma</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Clinical Esthetics Certificate of Excellence</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Advanced Makeup Certificate</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Laser Certificate of Attendance (provided by AMMP)</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\"><strong>Learned Skills and Acquired Knowledge</strong></h2>\r\nA graduate of Program will acquire knowledge and skills, which will allow them to work successfully in the field. The basic topics covered include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Basic Facials</li>\r\n 	<li>Makeup</li>\r\n 	<li>Basics of Chemistry</li>\r\n 	<li>Basics of Electricity</li>\r\n 	<li>Anatomy and Physiology</li>\r\n 	<li>Chemical peels</li>\r\n 	<li>Hair Removal</li>\r\n 	<li>Skin care products: Chemistry, Ingredients</li>\r\n 	<li>Product Sales</li>\r\n 	<li>Infection Control</li>\r\n 	<li>Facial Machines</li>\r\n 	<li>Physiology and Histology of Skin</li>\r\n 	<li>Product use for a different skin types</li>\r\n 	<li>Skin Analysis</li>\r\n 	<li>Facial Massage</li>\r\n 	<li>Skin Disorders</li>\r\n 	<li>Salon and Spa Business</li>\r\n 	<li>Professional Communication</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\"><strong>Additional Advanced Training</strong></h2>\r\nIn addition to the knowledge and skills, required by the State of Illinois and taught by other schools, our students learn advanced subjects and techniques!\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Medical Esthetics regulations</li>\r\n 	<li>Chemical Exfoliation (peels)</li>\r\n 	<li>Galvanic Skin care Treatments</li>\r\n 	<li>Ultrasound Skin care Treatments</li>\r\n 	<li>Lymphatic Drainage</li>\r\n 	<li>Cosmecuticals and Botanicals</li>\r\n 	<li>Acne Skin and Acne Skin Treatment</li>\r\n 	<li>Therapeutic Relaxation – Hands and Feet</li>\r\n 	<li>Man’s Facial</li>\r\n 	<li>Hot Stone Massage</li>\r\n 	<li>Eyebrow and Eyelash Tinting</li>\r\n 	<li>Brazilian</li>\r\n 	<li>False Eyelash Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Nose &amp; Ear waxing</li>\r\n 	<li>Salt Glow</li>\r\n 	<li>Age-Control™ Facial</li>\r\n 	<li>Mechanical Exfoliation</li>\r\n 	<li>Advanced Makeup</li>\r\n 	<li>Lymphatic System</li>\r\n 	<li>Rosacea Skin and Rosacea Skin Treatment</li>\r\n 	<li>Best anti-aging ingredients</li>\r\n 	<li>Aromatherapy</li>\r\n 	<li>Paraffin mask Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Back Treatment</li>\r\n 	<li>In-depth Anatomy and Physiology</li>\r\n 	<li>Speed Waxing</li>\r\n 	<li>False Eyelash Application</li>\r\n 	<li>Eyebrow Arch</li>\r\n 	<li>Body Wrap</li>\r\n 	<li>Entrepreneurship and Business Plan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\">Career Opportunities in Esthetics</h2>\r\nSkincare specialists provide facials procedures, full-body treatments, and hair removal services. Estheticians in clinical setting focus on providing additional skincare treatments, such as peels, Microdermabrasion, galvanic, ultrasound, and high-frequency.\r\n\r\nEstheticians who combine knowledge of their field, with skills, and business acumen, further their careers by taking on management positions and opening their own spas and medispas.\r\n<h2 class=\"cufon_headings\"><strong>Work Environment</strong></h2>\r\nSkincare specialists usually work in s