ass=\"p9\">Product use for a different skin types</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Anatomy and Physiology</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Skin Analysis</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Chemical peels</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Facial Massage</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Hair Removal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Skin Disorders</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Skin care products: Chemistry, Ingredients</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Salon and Spa Business</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Product Sales</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td class=\"td1\" valign=\"top\">\r\n<p class=\"p9\">Professional Communication</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"p7\">Certification and Licensure</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Students, who complete the entire 750-hour Program, receive the following:</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>Esthetics Diploma</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>Clinical Esthetics Certificate of Excellence</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>Advanced Makeup Certificate</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Laser Certificate of Attendance (provided by AMMP)</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b><i>The certificates are recognition of the student’s accomplishments!</i></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b><i>Students then allowed to apply for licensure state test.</i></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>Our in-depth presentations based on the medical sources and new researches in the medical field.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>We provide our students with extraordinary skills, extensive in-depth knowledge, and confidence needed for a personal success and successful employment!</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Although Estheticians cannot operate laser in Illinois, we believe that every person practicing Skin Care needs to have an extensive knowledge on the technologies used in skin care and a medical setting. Laser class for our students is provided by our partners and professionals in Laser technology: AAMP.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p12\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b> Our graduates have an excellent opportunity to also enroll in the  HYPERLINK \"http://itaskinbeauty.com/ma-program-description/\" </b><span class=\"s6\"><b><i>Medical Assisting Program</i></b></span><span class=\"s7\"><b>!</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Our Nationally Certified MA students are able to complete their externship at Rush University Medical School’s Dermatology Department. </b><span class=\"s7\"><b>In Illinois, Medical Assistants can be delegated by a Physician to perform Laser and Injections!</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p13\">Upcoming Start Dates</p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\"><span class=\"s5\"><b>Day/Full-time: </b></span>Monday – Thursday, 9 a.m. – 3:30 p.m.;<span class=\"s5\"><b> September 6, 2016</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p6\"><span class=\"s5\"><b>Evening/Part-time: </b></span>Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, 9 a.m. – 3:30 p.m<span class=\"s5\"><b>.; September 6, 2016</b></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>The Program takes approximately 5.5 months for full-time students and approximately 9 months for part-time students.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p10\"><b>Upon successful completion of the Esthetics Program, graduates are eligible to sign up for the State licensing exams. We are proud that our graduates have a 100% passing rate in Illinois and have some of the highest test scores nationally.</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p15\"><b><i>Career Outlook &amp; Opportunities in Esthetics</i></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\">Skincare specialists provide facials procedures, full-body treatments, and hair removal services. Estheticians in clinical setting focus on providing additional skincare treatments, such as peels, Microdermabrasion, galvanic, ultrasound, and high-frequency.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\">Estheticians who combine knowledge of their field, with skills, and business acumen, further their careers by taking on management positions and opening their own spas and medispas.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p7\">Work Environment</p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\">Skincare specialists usually work in salons, health and beauty spas, or medical offices. Most work full time. Many work evenings and weekends, especially self-employed workers operating their own salon. According to the US Labor Bureau, “skincare specialists held about 47,600 jobs in 2010, of which 47% worked in the personal care services industry. About 37% were self-employed”. Possibly because their job involves making others feel and look better, Estheticians report high levels of job satisfaction!</p>\r\n<p class=\"p8\">Esthetics employment is expected to grow 25% between 2010 and 2020, according to the US Labor Bureau, at a rate much faster than the average. Because of the aging population and cultural focus on staying healthy and looking good, Estheticians will continue to be in demand.</p>','750-Hour Esthetics (Aesthetics) Program','','inherit','closed','closed','','50-revision-v1','','','2016-08-21 11:10:47','2016-08-21 11:10:47','',50,'http://design-austin.com/ita/2016/08/21/50-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(228,1,'2016-08-21 11:11:18','2016-08-21 11:11:18','<p class=\"p1\"><b>ITA’s 750-hour Esthetics program goes above and beyond the state requirements!</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>The program does<i> </i>not exceed the scope of practice for Estheticians! <i> </i></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Skin care profession is clinical by its nature and requires a professional clinical setting!</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><b>Our</b><span class=\"s1\"> </span><b>750-hour Esthetics Program</b><span class=\"s1\"> </span><b>with advanced Clinical curriculum</b><span class=\"s1\"> </span><b>is designed to prepare Estheticians