Paramedical Clinical Aesthetics Program\" width=\"500\" height=\"440\" /></a>\n\nThe Program takes 6 days of intensive training and provides students with the latest Dermatology, skin care, and Medical Esthetics information. The program provides a revolutionary approach to skin care education by successfully combining medical knowledge with esthetics.\n<h2><em><strong> Upon Completion of the Program a student receives a Certificate of Attendance and a certificate of completion of 60 CEUs.</strong></em></h2>\n<h2><span style=\"color:#b8000d;\"><strong>The first class - Laser by AMMP - will take place on Saturday, May 3</strong></span></h2>\n<span style=\"color:#682501;\">You can sign up for each day separately. Every single day will provide you with 10 CEU certificate.</span>\n\n<span style=\"color:#682501;\">The cost of the entire program is $2,150.00 (you save $205.00). You can pay online, to reserve your spot!</span>','NEW Paramedical/Clinical Aesthetics Program!','','publish','open','open','','new-paramedicalclinical-aesthetics-program','','','2014-04-24 12:36:07','2014-04-24 17:36:07','',0,'http://intlacademy.wordpress.com/?p=5213',0,'post','',0),(5216,2,'2014-04-24 12:34:41','2014-04-24 17:34:41','','60-Hr CE Paramedical Clinical Aesthetics Program','','inherit','open','open','','60-hr-ce-paramedical-clinical-aesthetics-program','','','2014-04-24 12:34:41','2014-04-24 17:34:41','',5213,'http://design-austin.com/ita/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/60-hr-ce-paramedical-clinical-aesthetics-program.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(6272,2,'2014-05-09 14:32:22','2014-05-09 19:32:22','<strong>Here is another post from our Esthetics student, Alissa:</strong>\n\nWe all are different. We all are learning the same things, the same massages, same techniques, but it is never truly the same. We all put a bit of ourselves into what we do. Learning massage has been my favorite part thus far. The mannequins are not too flexible, hard, and kind of hurt the hands. They are rather difficult client, but I understand that we need to start on them before on a person. Practicing on another student is a whole different experience. Massage is something that I felt I was able to understand when Dr. Doran instructed the class a couple weeks ago. We had to close our eyes, and feel. We had to feel the muscles and bones. Being the one practiced on is helpful for developing your own massage. Something one might feel, for example on the jawline, may make one believe they are causing discomfort to the client. Being the client, one realizes it does not cause discomfort what-so-ever. With that knowledge, it does not make one feel uncomfortable preforming the move and in turn makes the client more relaxed. The client can only be as relaxed as you are.\n\nNow waxing is a different story. Waxing has been something I have been practiced on more often than not. One has to realize you have to go out of your comfort zone in both waxing and being waxed. Students need to practice on one another. I have now had two Brazilian waxing procedures. This time it hurt still, but not like the first time. It does get better as you continue to be waxed. Waxing is something that is different for everyone. Some people, like me, feel some pain and discomfort when legs are waxed. On the other hand, some don’t feel pain; another student loves how waxing feels on her legs. People should not be afraid of waxing because of potential pain, but should expect some. If you go in with the right mind-set, it is not that bad.\n\nTo me, it is rather strange but nice that an Esthetician knows a little of a lot. We go over basics of electricity, basics of nutrition, etc. It is nice to learn a bit of everything, but I am a person who likes to go a bit deeper, to try to go beyond the basics. This has been a nice way to gain a bit of everything but leave room for the bigger subjects that we need to know, like skin histology and physiology and skin disorders. Haven’t gotten there yet, but we are about to start them','Student\'s Story Continues','','publish','open','open','','studentsstory','','','2014-05-09 14:32:22','2014-05-09 19:32:22','',0,'http://intlacademy.wordpress.com/?p=6272',0,'post','',0),(8523,2,'2014-05-22 21:05:35','2014-05-23 02:05:35','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iytRPTdwgP4\n\n<p>We are so excited to have Ms. Julia Bowers teach the Permanent Makeup Program on July 26. This video clearly showcases why Ms. Julia is one of the best permanent makeup artists in the worlds! She does it all - from camouflaging scars, to filling in receding hairlines, to reconstructing areolas, to creating beautiful lip and eye-lines, to tattooing beautiful and natural-looking eyebrows!</p>','Permanent Makeup Portfolio','','publish','open','open','','permanent-makeup-portfolio','','','2014-05-22 21:05:35','2014-05-23 02:05:35','',0,'http://intlacademy.wordpress.com/?p=8523',0,'post','',0),(10468,2,'2014-06-01 18:24:36','2014-06-01 23:24:36','<img src=\"http://intlacademy.files.wordpress.com/2014/06/go-get-them-tigers-ita.jpg\" class=\"size-full\" alt=\"GO GET THEM, TIGERS!\" />\n\n<p>Several of our recent grads are taking their State exam tomorrow! We are not going to wish them good luck - because they don\'t need luck !\n\nThey are the most knowledgeable, intelligent, and professional! (Basically Skin Care Rock stars!)You are the best of the best of the best!\n\nGO GET THEM, TIGERS!</p>','GO GET THEM, TIGERS!','','publish','open','open','','go-get-them-tigers','','','2014-06-01 18:24:36','2014-06-01 23:24:36','',0,'http://intlacademy.wordpress.com/?p=10468',0,'post','',0),(11383,2,'2014-06-23 15:50:38','2014-06-23 20:50:38','<strong> NEED TO FINANCE YOUR EDUCATION? Now you have even more options!  Get a loan for up to 5  years!</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://Prosper.evyy.net/c/94845/67132/994\"><img src=\"http://adn.impactradius.com/display-ad/994-67132\" alt=\"\" width=\"728\" height=\"90\" border=\"0\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Or apply with a co-signer!</strong>\n\nIf y