found within them which protect against ultraviolet rays, giving you a clearer complexion. As well, tomatoes have a high amount of Vitamin C to brighten skin to give the skin a radiant glow. There are many ways to use tomatoes on your skin in many different facial masks.\n<ol>\n	<li>Wash the medium size tomato and peel the skin off. Next, extract and strain its water content and mix it with flour to create a paste. Apply the mask and leave it on your face for 5 minutes and rinse with water. If you feel like your skin tends to be dry you can add olive oil in the mask in order to give your skin more of a combination skin.</li>\n	<li>Take one tomato and lemon, squeeze out their juice and mix them together. Apply the mask and leave on your face for 30 minutes, then rinse with water. This mask tightens your skin and delay the ageing of your skin. If one happens to have dry skin add a little of honey and olive oil to the mask.</li>\n	<li>Take an orange, tomato and cucumber, squeeze their juice and mix together. Apply to your face before bed for 30 minutes than rinse with water. This mask diminishes pigmentation marks on your skin and improves skin complexion.</li>\n	<li>If you tend to have many open pores and want to treat them, add four drops of tomato juice and 1 teaspoon of water, apply with a cotton ball to your face. Gently massage your skin and leave it on for 15 minutes and rinse with water. Giving you a smaller pore size.</li>\n</ol>\nWho would have thought that a tomato could do so much for your skin! These are easy mask to do at home in order to maintain that healthy, glowing looking skin\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n.<a href=\"http://allindiaroundup.com/beauty/amazing-beauty-benefits-tomatoes-say-yes-tomato-facial-mask-no-wrinkles/\">Article </a>\n\n&nbsp;','Tomatoes for a Facial Mask?','','publish','open','open','','do-you-want-a-facial-mask-that-can-make-your-skin-look-healthier','','','2016-07-15 12:36:13','2016-07-15 17:36:13','',0,'https://intlacademy.wordpress.com/?p=11522',0,'post','',0),(11523,1,'2016-08-26 14:04:56','2016-08-26 14:04:56','<h2 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">What does</span> an Esthetician Do?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Skincare specialists (estheticians) provide facials procedures, full-body treatments, and hair removal services. Medical Estheticians focus on providing additional skincare treatments, such as peels, Microdermabrasion, galvanic, ultrasound, and high-frequency.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Estheticians who combine knowledge of their field, with skills, and business acumen, further their careers by taking on management positions and opening their own spas and medispas.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p3\">What is working as an Esthetician like?</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><b>Skincare specialists (estheticians)</b> usually work in salons, health and beauty spas, or medical offices. Most work full time. Many work evenings and weekends, especially self-employed workers operating their own salon. According to the US Labor Bureau, “skincare specialists held about 47,600 jobs in 2010, of which 47% worked in the personal care services industry. About 37% were self-employed”.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Possibly because their job involves making others feel and look better, <b>Estheticians report high levels of job satisfaction!</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\"><b>Esthetics teachers </b>teach students the practices of skin care, waxing, tweezing, body treatments and makeup application. Work environment is pleasant and includes private schools, community colleges, continuing education centers, and work with State boards.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">What are the Career Opportunities for an Esthetician?</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">An esthetician has a lot of opportunities. First of all, they can move to other States and apply for State Licensing there. Secondly, the esthetician can get a job she is passionate about. Some of the choices include:</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">Practitioner in Medical Practices:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul cla